## Round 5 (source B) — del/path + verify families, live probing (ports 3100-3103)
# Own wrapper scratch/wl_server5.sh (--port= form, ports 3100-3199). Theory
# RevealingSignatures (regression/trace/issue193.spthy, one exists-trace lemma
# `debug`) for trace; jcs19-xor/diff-models/KCL07-UK1_attack-manual.spthy for equiv.
# Motivated by round5/ORACLE_NOTES.md: the round-4 del/verify NEGATIVE ([R47]) was a
# probe-shape artifact — both routes take a further TWO-segment theory sub-path.
[R50] verify family reproduces the staged captures (:3100/:3101 trace, v1) |
      GET verify/lemma/debug -> 200 json {html,title} BYTE-IDENTICAL to main/help
      (title "Theory: RevealingSignatures"); == round5/verify.json (modulo non-det
      Loaded-at time + tmp path). GET verify/proof/debug -> 200 json
      {"redirect":"/thy/trace/1/overview/proof/debug"} == round5/verify_proof.json.
      Neither allocates a version (v2=404 after) -> verify NEVER mutates/bumps.
[R51] verify decision rule (redirect vs content), trace | GET verify/<theory-path>:
      proof/<lemma> where the LEMMA EXISTS -> {redirect:/thy/trace/<idx>/overview/
      proof/<lemma>[/path]} at the SAME idx (redirect target = overview/ + verbatim
      input path; verify/proof/debug/_/ONE/ONE -> .../overview/proof/debug/_/ONE/ONE).
      Everything else -> {html,title} = the help pane (== main/help): rules, message,
      tactic, help, cases/raw/0/0, lemma/<any>, method/L/n, add/edit/delete/<x>, AND
      proof/<NONEXISTENT-lemma>. A bogus SUBNODE of a real lemma still redirects
      (verify/proof/debug/BOGUS -> redirect) -> predicate = lemma existence, not
      full-path resolution. verify content byte-identical to main/help for rules/
      message/tactic/cases/add/edit/delete (7/7 cmp).
[R52] del/path family reproduces the staged captures (:3100/:3101 trace) |
      GET del/path/lemma/debug -> 200 json {"redirect":"/thy/trace/<new>/overview/
      lemma/debug"} at a FRESH version (== round5/del_path.json shape; capture idx 5
      because prior ops existed, fresh server -> idx 2). GET del/path/rules -> 200
      json {"alert":"Can't delete the given theory path!"} == round5/del_path_bad.json,
      no bump.
[R53] del/path redirect target + version model | redirect = overview/ + verbatim
      input path, at a freshly allocated index: del/path/lemma/debug->overview/lemma/
      debug; del/path/proof/debug->overview/proof/debug; del/path/proof/debug/_/ONE->
      overview/proof/debug/_/ONE. Each deletable op allocates a NEW index (v2..v8
      created one-per-redirect), base retained. => del/path (deletable) is a PROOF OP
      (new index off the global monotonic counter), NOT an in-place structural edit.
      Proved: autoprove debug->v2 SOLVED; del/path/proof/debug on v2 -> v3 reset to
      "by sorry" (deletion persists in the new version), v2 STILL SOLVED (base kept).
[R54] del/path deletability + THREE alert strings, selected by path TYPE (trace) |
      lemma/<existing> & proof/<existing-lemma>[/...] -> REDIRECT+new version.
      lemma/<nonexistent> -> {"alert":"Sorry, but removing the selected lemma failed!"}.
      proof/<nonexistent-lemma OR bogus subnode> -> {"alert":"Sorry, but removing the
      selected proof step failed!"}. help/message/rules/tactic/cases/raw/0/0/method/
      add/edit/delete -> {"alert":"Can't delete the given theory path!"} (never
      deletable, no bump, no prover mutation).
[R55] Route registration + method + parse ordering (OVERTURNS round-4 [R47]) | del/path
      and verify are REGISTERED. Both GET-only: a wrong method (POST/PUT/DELETE) on a
      PARSEABLE theory-path -> 405 Method-Not-Supported page (byte-identical to
      r4_badmethod_post_kill.html for POST); a wrong method on an UNPARSEABLE tail ->
      404. GET on unparseable tail -> 404. => method dispatch happens AFTER the
      theory-path PathMultiPiece parse: unparseable=route miss (404 any method),
      parseable+wrongmethod=405. The round-4 sweep used bogus segments (x/y/z) that
      never parse as theory paths, so it only hit the 404 branch. 404 body echoes the
      FULL request path (<p>/thy/trace/1/del/path/x</p>), same notfound template.
[R56] Theory-path grammar is MODE-DEPENDENT at the route/parse level | TRACE parses
      {help,message,rules,tactic,cases/{raw|refined}/L/N,lemma/N,proof/L[/...],
      method/L/N,add/P,edit/N,delete/N}; 404 on {sources,cases(bare),diffProof,
      diffrules,x,...}. EQUIV (--diff, DiffTheoryPath) parses {help,diffrules,
      diffProof/L[/side...],diffMethod/L/N}; 404 on {message,tactic,cases,rules,proof,
      lemma,add,edit,delete,method}. Confirmed by 404-on-both-methods vs 405-on-POST.
[R57] Mode asymmetry of the two families | del/path is registered in BOTH trace and
      equiv. verify is registered in TRACE ONLY: in equiv every verify/<x> (incl.
      diffProof/help) returns 404 for GET *and* POST -> route genuinely absent under
      --diff. EQUIV del/path: diffProof/<existing> -> {redirect:/thy/equiv/<new>/
      overview/diffProof/<lemma>[/path]} new version; diffProof/<nonexistent|bogus> ->
      {"alert":"Sorry, but removing the selected proof step failed!"}; help/diffrules/
      diffMethod -> {"alert":"Can't delete the given theory path!"}.

